latestPosts.caption:
Love me some affordable Aussie makeup! 😙🥰

I’ve been a long time fan of @australiscosmetics and as an oily combo girly, I adore their fresh and flawless range. So obviously, I was stoked when they sent over these new goodies from the same range. I’ve only tried the powder so far and really enjoy that as it’s so finely milled and keeps my oils at bay. I’ll have to try the rest when I’ve got a moment to sit down and play around with makeup. 

Some of my personal faves from this brand are:
- fresh & flawless full coverage foundation
- fresh & flawless pressed powder
- dewy + daring cream blush
- dewy + daring cream bronzer
- lip glaze
- neutralize nude eyeshadow palette 

What’s your favourite drugstore makeup brand?

Just a few unopened Korean skincare items I really need to get to or stash away. This year, I’ve had the pleasure of being a @stylekorean_global ambassador which has given me the opportunity to receive so many products to try out. 

I often think back to 2018 when I decided to create this page after much encouragement from my friends to share my thoughts on beauty products. If I had not done so, I wouldn’t be here being able to try out brands and items that I could have only ever dreamed of before. It’s the longest project I’ve ever worked on!

While my page isn’t huge, I am still so grateful and humble of the connections I’ve formed on here and how it’s allowed me to meet so many great people.

Thank you so much for giving a damn about what I say on here. It means so much to me. ❤️

Here are the skincare and hair care products I packed on my quick trip to Vietnam for my grandmother’s funeral. I had booked very last minute flights and because they were last minute, they were also expensive and so I decided to forego checked in baggage. I was only going to be there for a few days and felt that I didn’t need it, if I was going to be completely honest with myself. 

Me being such a maximalist when it comes to packing and also my skincare, I panicked a little, BUT ALL WAS WELL. I managed to pack everything I needed in under 7kg for 4 days. I even ended up bringing back souvenirs for my children and nephew and Vietnamese coffee for my best friend! I am absolutely so impressed with myself. 

Are you a serial over-packer or under packer OR are you a rare one to be able to pack the right amount?
